    "No matter how the protein is rotated or translated, the angles specifying the next atom given the current atom never change.",
    "In fact, we demonstrate that our model becomes brittle upon substituting our translation-and rotation-invariant internal angle representation with Cartesian coordinates, keeping all other design choices identical (Figure S6).",
